      "content": "it’s not just technical degradation though. the way certain specific lunar landing telemetry logs from the late 60s were \"lost\" or \"misplaced\" feels too convenient. it’s a pattern we see in other classified programs too—where things are scrubbed to maintain a certain narrative. if we look at the timeline of when the public narrative shifted from \"exploration\" to \"proving we were there\" right after the missions, it doesn't track. don't you think it's worth investigating if these data gaps correlate with any specific declassification periods or government containment protocols from that era?",
